{"id":"2302.13197","submitter":"Songling Shan","authors":"Michael J. Plantholt and Songling Shan","title":"Chromatic index of multigraphs with high minimum degree","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A subgraph $H$ of a multigraph $G$ is overfull if $ |E(H) | > \\Delta(G)\n\\lfloor |V(H)|/2 \\rfloor.$ Analogous to the Overfull Conjecture proposed by\nChetwynd and Hilton in 1986, one can form its multigraph version as follows:\nLet $G$ be a multigraph with maximum multiplicity $r$ and maximum degree\n$\\Delta>\\frac{1}{3} r|V(G)|$. Then $G$ has chromatic index $\\Delta(G)$ if and\nonly if $G$ contains no overfull subgraph. In this paper, we prove the\nfollowing three results toward the Multigraph Overfull Conjecture for\nsufficiently large and even $n$.\n  (1) If $G$ is $k$-regular with $k\\ge r(n/2+18)$, then $G$ has a\n1-factorization.\n  (2) If $G$ contains an overfull subgraph and $\\delta(G)\\ge r(n/2+18)$, then\n$\\chi'(G)=\\lceil \\chi'_f(G) \\rceil$, where $\\chi'_f(G)$ is the fractional\nchromatic index of $G$.\n  (3) If the minimum degree of $G$ is at least $(1+\\varepsilon)rn/2$ for any\n$0<\\varepsilon<1$ and $G$ contains no overfull subgraph, then\n$\\chi'(G)=\\Delta(G)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 26 Feb 2023 00:18:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-28"}
